column1: Information on the Medicine Shortage Reports Database

The TGA publishes information about medicines in Australia that are in shortage, may shortly become subject to shortage or have been discontinued from supply. This information is based on details provided to the TGA by sponsors and is published on the TGA’s Medicine Shortage Reports Database.
More information about medicine shortages is available at https://www.tga.gov.au/hubs/medicine-shortages.
About the release of this information

While reasonable care is taken to ensure that the information is an accurate record of medicine shortages or discontinuations of supply that responsible entities have reported to the TGA, the TGA does not guarantee or warrant the accuracy, reliability, completeness or currency of the information (particularly as the Medicine Shortage Reports Database is subject to frequent updates because of the mandatory reporting requirements) or its usefulness in achieving any purpose.

To the fullest extent permitted by law, including but not limited to section 61A of the Therapeutic Goods Act 1989, the TGA will not be liable for any loss, damage, cost or expense incurred in or arising by reason of any person relying on this information.
